---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Meta | Work Experience | Sam Lee" description="Technical Artist work at Meta Reality Labs, developing tools and environments for Horizon Home.">
  <section class="container py-12 md:py-16">
    <header class="mb-12">
      <nav class="mb-6">
        <a href="/work-experience" class="inline-flex items-center text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 hover:text-accent transition-colors">
          <svg class="w-4 h-4 mr-1" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M15 19l-7-7 7-7" />
          </svg>
          Back to Work Experience
        </a>
      </nav>

      <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-6">
        <img src="/images/logos/meta-logo.png" alt="Meta logo" class="w-16 h-16 object-contain flex-shrink-0 rounded-2xl" />
        <div>
          <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Meta</h1>
          <p class="text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">Technical Artist, Reality Labs</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 dark:text-gray-500">June 2024 – Present</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
        I joined Meta as a contract Technical Artist in June 2024 and converted to a full-time employee in March 2025.
        I develop tools and workflows that power Meta's virtual reality experiences,
        working at the intersection of Unreal Engine and <a href="https://developers.meta.com/horizon/blog/studio/meta-horizon-engine-at-a-glance/" target="_blank" class="text-accent hover:underline">Meta Horizon Engine</a>.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div>
      <!-- Project: Horizon Home Switchable Vistas -->
      <article class="mb-16">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100 mb-2">Horizon Home Switchable Vistas</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 dark:text-gray-500 mb-4">2025</p>

        <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert mb-6">
          <p>
            Productionized "Switchable Vista" homes—high-fidelity virtual environments that users can seamlessly
            switch between as their VR home space. These environments are built using Meta Horizon Engine to
            deliver rich, immersive experiences on Quest hardware.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-8 mb-8">
          <div>
            <video
              src="/images/work-experiences/meta/DEV_2025_HSR_04_enviroments_091725_TP-1.mov"
              class="w-full rounded-lg"
              controls
              autoplay
              loop
              muted
              playsinline
            ></video>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-2">High-fidelity environment showcase</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <video
              src="/images/work-experiences/meta/DEV_2025_HSR_02_Home_UI_091725_TP-1.mov"
              class="w-full rounded-lg"
              controls
              autoplay
              loop
              muted
              playsinline
            ></video>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-2">Home UI navigation between Vista environments</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <video
              src="/images/work-experiences/meta/DEV_2025_HSR_03_browser_IG_091725_New clip_TP-1.mov"
              class="w-full rounded-lg"
              controls
              autoplay
              loop
              muted
              playsinline
            ></video>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-2">Browser and instagram panels with custom shading</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-8">
          <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 rounded-full text-sm">Unreal Engine</span>
          <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 rounded-full text-sm">Meta Horizon Engine</span>
          <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 rounded-full text-sm">Python</span>
          <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 rounded-full text-sm">C++</span>
          <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 rounded-full text-sm">Light Baking</span>
          <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 rounded-full text-sm">VR Development</span>
        </div>

        <img
          src="/images/work-experiences/meta/end-of-year-recap-hzos-events-tech-art-team-meta-reality-labs-google-docs.png"
          alt="Horizon Home environments shipped in 2024"
          class="w-full rounded-lg border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 mb-8"
        />

        <h4 class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100 mb-3">Contributions</h4>
        <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert">
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Light baking workflows</strong> — Developed Unreal Engine tooling for baking high-quality lightmaps optimized for mobile VR</li>
            <li><strong>Asset export pipelines</strong> — Built tools for processing and exporting assets from Unreal to Meta Horizon Engine</li>
            <li><strong>Creator tooling</strong> — Collaborated closely with MHE engineers to improve the tooling experience for content creators</li>
            <li><strong>Light probe system</strong> — Authored a light probe tool that dynamically lights all avatars in Horizon Home and Events, ensuring visual consistency across different spaces and lighting conditions</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </article>

      <!-- Add more projects here -->

    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
